@page "/getting-started"

<PageTitle>Getting Started — Djehuti Teacher</PageTitle>

<div class="teacher-page">
    <h1>Getting Started</h1>

    <div class="teacher-hero-grid">
        <div class="teacher-hero-card">
            <h2>1. Browse or build</h2>
            <p>Head to the <a href="catalog">Catalog</a> to find something to learn, or open <a href="your-lessons">Your Lessons</a> to create a lesson plan of your own — any subject, not just math.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="teacher-hero-card">
            <h2>2. Read for free</h2>
            <p>Every lesson's written content, reference links, and videos are free to read — no key required. Sign in to track your progress across sessions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="teacher-hero-card">
            <h2>3. Add a key for live tutoring</h2>
            <p>Visit <a href="ai-setup">AI Setup</a> to add your own AI provider key. That's what powers the interactive part: an AI that asks guiding questions and works through problems with you, deliberately built to build understanding rather than hand you the answer.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="teacher-page-section">
        <h2>A note on how the AI teaches</h2>
        <p class="teacher-page-subtitle">
            Djehuti Teacher's tutoring is instructed to prioritize comprehension over completion. If you ask it
            for the answer to a problem, expect it to ask you a question back first. The goal is that you leave
            a lesson actually understanding the material, not just having copied a correct result.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
